{
  "texts": [
    "One of first readout error mitigation schemes was applied to two superconducting transmon qubits 140.",
    "The method was extended using quantum detector tomography an tested on IBM and Rigetti quantum computers 141.",
    "In its pure form readout error mitigation requires calibration measurements on all possible quantum states, leading to an exponential increase in required measurements.",
    "However, if the readout errors are only partially correlated, e.g.",
    "due to the local structure of the qubits, tensored readout error mitigation overcomes this issue 142."
  ]
}